CRUD OPERATION IN MongoDB..


(CRUD)

CREATE
Creation and insertion in MongoDB. As We know that mongodb is document
oriented database. so a collection will be containing multiple documents.

Collection Creation: To create a collection in the mongodb, we can use the
createCollection() method.

Syntax: db.createCollection().

Document Insertion: To insert document in collection, we have to use the
insert() method.

Syntax: db.<collection_name>.insert(document)

the documents should be in JSON format.


READ
Reade opration from MongoDB Collections: To reade the document from the
collection we can use the find() method. and documents are containing Key value pairs

Syntax: db.<collection_name>.find()

To display the result in a better way, we can use the pretty() method.

Syntax: db.<collection_name>.find().pretty()


UPDATE:
To update the document we will use the update() method for the first match
and updateMany() for all documents.

Syntax: db.<collection_name>.update(<selection_logic>,<Updated_Data>)


DELETE:
To delete the document we will use the remove() method.
Syntax: db.<collection_name>.remove(<selection_logic>) 

To remove all entries, we use remove command like this.
Syntax: db.<collection_name>.remove({}).
